    public abstract class AmpCategoryFieldPanel
extends AmpFieldPanel<AmpCategoryValue>
    This class is used by all Category manager controls on the page, by subclassing and implementing constructors that populate the choiceContainer based on what type of control we have (group or select)

      • AmpCategoryFieldPanel

        public AmpCategoryFieldPanel(java.lang.String id,
                             java.lang.String categKey,
                             java.lang.String fmName,
                             boolean ordered,
                             java.lang.Boolean isMultiselect,
                             org.apache.wicket.model.IModel<java.util.Set<AmpCategoryValue>> relatedChoicesModel,
                             boolean hideLabel,
                             boolean hideNewLine)
                      throws java.lang.Exception
        Constructs a category field panel used by all types of category manager controls.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the control on the page
        categoryKey - the category key of the category displayed
        fmName - the feature manager name from FM
        ordered - if this category list is ordered
        isMultiselect - if this category is multiselect. Use null here to read the database state of this category, or true/false to override that behavior
        relatedChoicesModel - if this parameter is not null, it will be used to iterate all AmpCategoryValueS and retrieve the AmpCategoryValue.getUsedByValues() for each, making sure this control only displays AmpCategoryValueS that are used by the related AmpCategoryValueS This is used to filter linked categories
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
        See Also:
        CategoryConstants.IMPLEMENTATION_LEVEL_NAME, CategoryConstants.IMPLEMENTATION_LOCATION_NAME
